Helen situated her bag behind her, on top of some of the other packs on Bitterbark’s back. “Well, it’s no surprise why they call it the Ice Wastes.” Helen said when she finally looked up, around the area. The place was flat, and empty. Spikes of ice hung from the ceiling and jutted from the ground. It seemed that there was more ice than stone here. “Wait... what is that?” Smokeswirl said, whiskers twitching as a familiar scent reached her nose. “I smell death.” The Gnawer followed the scent, but didn’t need to travel far to find the source. Or, more specifically, sources. Blending in with the ice, frozen to the ground, was a Prowler corpse. And, a few paces down, another. They were hard to notice at first, but they were numerous. “Oh, dear...” Demeter said, wrinkling her nose. “This place is awful.”
Presley 15-Jul-20 08:27 PM
Bitterbark walked up to one of the corpses and nudged it. It was like nudging rock. The bodies were frozen solid. "They just all died here?" He questioned aloud, suspicious. (edited)
Lenn 15-Jul-20 08:52 PM
“Prowlers often come here to die. The old, the sick, those who cannot fend for themselves and want to speed up the process... but most of the corpses are from the unlucky souls who were banished. They’re sent here to ‘fend for themselves.’ But it’s really a death sentence.” Keene said. “They will lessen as we go on.”
Presley 15-Jul-20 09:03 PM
"Tidy," Ripred sniffed sarcastically, giving the bodies a wide berth as he walked through the chilled graves. Josephix knelt beside one of the bodies, hands hovering above the ice-covered corpse. "Some look like they just went to sleep..." A less painful way to go, but terrible nonetheless.
Lenn 15-Jul-20 09:17 PM
Helen was shrinking away from the bodies, trying not to look, but they drew her eyes anyway. She felt sick. Even if she couldn’t smell them. “Yes, that’s what happens when you start to freeze. You get sleepy. So if, by any chance, you’re caught alone in the cold, try not to sleep. You likely won’t wake up.” Keene advised. The dangers of frostbite were drilled into Prowler pups.
